-- Central European Media Rises to 3-Week High for Best Month in 6
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-04-27T12:51:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/central-european-media-rises-to-3-week-high-for-best-month-in-6.html
Central European Media Enterprises
Ltd. (CETV)  jumped to the highest in more than three weeks in Czech
trading, headed for its biggest monthly rally since October.  CME, as the television broadcaster is known, increased 4.7
percent to 146 koruna, the strongest price since April 4. The
stock has gained 10 percent this week and 8.2 percent in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
